 Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1485–":"1485–Deceased","1485–Male":"1485–Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1487–Female":"1487–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1455–Male":"1455–Deceased","1559–Female":"1559–Deceased","1455":"1455","1487":"1487","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","of,Abertawe,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Swansea, Swansea, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fleming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Fleming was born in 1485, in Swansea, Swansea, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Fleming, was 31 and his mother, Alice ferch Llywelyn, was -73. He had at least 1 son with Angharad ferch Jenkin."},"et":{"1485–":"1485–Surnud","1485–Male":"1485–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1487–Female":"1487–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1455–Male":"1455–Surnud","1559–Female":"1559–Surnud","1455":"1455","1487":"1487","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","of,Abertawe,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Swansea, Swansea, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–":"1485–Kuollut","1485–Male":"1485–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1487–Female":"1487–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1455–Male":"1455–Kuollut","1559–Female":"1559–Kuollut","1455":"1455","1487":"1487","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","of,Abertawe,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Swansea, Swansea, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1485–":"1485–Décédé","1485–Male":"1485–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1487–Female":"1487–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1455–Male":"1455–Décédé","1559–Female":"1559–Décédée","1455":"1455","1487":"1487","1485":"1485","1559":"1559","of,Abertawe,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Swansea, Swansea, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Fleming est né en 1485, à Swansea, Swansea, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, Fleming, avait 31 ans et sa mère, Alice ferch Llywelyn, avait -73 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Angharad ferch Jenkin."},"de":{"148